=== Beyond Binary: Effect Magnitude, Timing, and Dose-Response as Diagnostic Dimensions
  <sec:beyond-binary>

*Certainty: 0.20.* The subclassification of response into magnitude, timing, and dose-response dimensions is mechanistic inference layered on already-inferential cascade logic. No ME/CFS study has employed these dimensions as formal diagnostic criteria.
The chapter so far classifies each probe result as binary: works / doesn't work. But the *shape* of response — how much, how fast, how long, at what dose — contains orthogonal diagnostic information that binary classification discards.

